white supremacist Anton Pretorius and suffered years of sexual abuse from him. When T'Challa found out where his mother was kept, he donned the Black Panther costume and rescued his mother. When Anton insisted that he loved her, Ramonda punched him in the face and left with her son.<ref>''Marvel Comics Presents'' #36-37</ref><ref>''Black Panther: Panther's Prey'' #1</ref>\n\nWhen Birnin Zana was attacked by terrorists, Ramonda was seriously injured, suffering several fractures and ending up in a coma.<ref>''Black Panther'' Vol. 6 #4</ref><ref>''Black Panther'' Vol. 6 #10</ref> She eventually came out of her coma and, despite the possibility of paralysis, managed to heal somewhat and now walks with a cane.<ref>''Black Panther'' Vol. 6 #12</ref><ref>''Black Panther'' Vol. 6 #16</ref>\n\n==In other media==\n===Television===\nAlthough not referred to by name, Ramonda appears in the animated ''[[Black Panther (TV series)|Black Panther]]'' series voiced by [[Alfre Woodard]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Voice Of Queen Mother - Black Panther <nowiki>|</nowiki> Behind The Voice Actors | url=http://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/tv-shows/Black-Panther/Queen-Mother/ | work=Behind The Voice Actors | accessdate=March 12, 2018| postscript=. Check mark indicates role has been confirmed using screenshots of closing credits and other reliable sources}}</ref> She was simply referred to as Queen Mother.\n\n===Film===\n* [[Angela Bassett]] portrays Ramonda in the 2018 film ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]'' as T'Challa and Shuri's mother and Queen Mother of Wakanda.<ref name=\"Bassett\">{{cite web|url=https://news.marvel.com/movies/55317/angela-bassett-boards-marvels-black-panther/ |title=Angela Bassett Boards Marvel's \"Black Panther\" |last=Morse |first=Ben |publisher=[[Marvel Comics|Marvel.com]] |date=November 21, 2016 |accessdate=November 21, 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6mC4Xi7BJ?url=https://news.marvel.com/movies/55317/angela-bassett-boards-marvels-black-panther/ |archivedate=November 21, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> Boseman noted that Ramonda \"is one of the advisors that [T'Challa] would look to... for some of the answers of what his father might want or might do. She may not be exactly right all the time, but she definitely has insights.\"<ref name=\"EWCoverJuly2017\">{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/movies/2017/07/12/black-panther-godfather-007-wakanda-royal-portrait/|title=How Black Panther aims to be the superhero version of The Godfather and 007|last=Breznican|first=Anthony|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=July 12, 2017|accessdate=July 12, 2017|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6rtynVSne?url=http://ew.com/movies/2017/07/12/black-panther-godfather-007-wakanda-royal-portrait/|archivedate=July 12, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Bassett wore a silver, waist-length wig for the role that was made from 120 pieces of hair hand-rolled into dreadlocks.<ref name=\"PressKit\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wdsmediafile.com/media/BlackPanther/writen-material/BlackPanther5a7e0853a38c3.pdf|title=''Black Panther'' Press Kit|publisher=[[Disney]]|accessdate=February 16, 2018|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6xGWPRCsn?url=http://www.wdsmediafile.com/media/BlackPanther/writen-material/BlackPanther5a7e0853a38c3.pdf|archivedate=February 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Corey Calliet served as Bassett's trainer, working with her before she began filming, and while she was on set, by creating [[high-intensity interval training]] circuits and helping to craft her diet.<ref name=\"BassettTrainer\">{{cite web|url=http://people.com/bodies/angela-bassett-black-panther-workout/ |title=Here's How Angela Bassett Will Shape Up for Marvel's Black Panther |last=Olya |first=Gabrielle |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=March 2, 2017 |accessdate=March 6, 2017 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6omBLL2z6?url=http://people.com/bodies/angela-bassett-black-panther-workout/ |archivedate=March 7, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> This version of Ramonda is the actual birth mother of T'Challa rather than his stepmother.\n* Bassett reprises the role in the 2019 film ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/avengers-endgame-cast-every-character-return/|title=Every Character In Avengers: Endgame|first1=Cooper|last1=Hood|work=Screen Rant|date=April 27, 2019|accessdate=April 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://comicbookdb.com/character.php?ID=30550 Ramonda] at the Comic Book DB\n*[https://www.comics.org/search.lasso/?sort=chrono&query=Ramonda&type=character Ramonda] at the [[Grand Comics Database]]\n\n{{Black Panther}}\n\n[[Category:Characters created by Don McGregor]]\n[[Category:Characters created by Gene Colan]]\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 1989]]\n[[Category:Female characters in comics]]\n[[Category:Female characters in film]]\n[[Category:Fictional queens]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics characters]]\n[[Category:Wakandans]]"}]}}}}